h1 Welcome to Beer &amp;&amp; Code Seattle
#content_text
  p Beer &amp;&amp; Code is a bi&ndash;weekly Seattle meetup. Participants meet at least one of these criteria:  
  ul
    li Uses any programming language for work or for fun
    li Enjoys having a tasty drink while using aforementioned programming language
    li Likes the idea of meeting other Beer &amp;&amp; Coders and building community
    li Thinks that being challenged by and learning from others is a great idea
  p Sound cool so far? Head over to the <a href="/calendar">Calendar</a> and come to our next meetup.
  p If you're new, here are some common questions you might have:  
  ul
    li I'm just learning programming and I'm a noob. Should I come? 
      span.faq_answer Yes
    li I'm actually a designer and I use BLAH BLAH BLAH. Should I come? 
      span.faq_answer Yes!
    li I don't have anything to work on. Should I come? 
      span.faq_answer Yes! (we'll find you something)                
  p At the risk of sounding repetitive, Beer &amp;&amp; Code is for <strong>anyone</strong>.
  p We meet at 7 pm and our location changes every few months.
  p We like beer. We like code. We like people. Come hang out with us.
  p If you're still interested in learning more, feel free to get in touch with us.
  p Check out our 
    a(href="https://groups.google.com/forum/#!forum/beer-code-seattle", target="_blank") Google Group
    |  or join us on IRC at #BeerAndCodeSeattle on the freenode (irc.freenode.net) network.
